<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1035,1889]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,1035,1061]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">Type data:</emphasis>
This species was described based on specimens of both sexes collected by the Lutheran pastor and amateur entomologist Gotthilf Birkmann (1854‒1944) in Fedor, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[972,1124,1071,1097]" name="United States of America" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">United States</collectingCountry>
. Birkmann began collecting insects about 1885 and continued to do so until 1920. In 1899, he published a list of 307 species and varieties of bees and wasps collected at Fedor (
<bibRefCitation author="Burke, H. R." box="[487,623,1143,1170]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" refId="ref20961" refString="Burke, H. R. (2016) Birkmann, Gotthilf. Handbook of Texas Online. Available from: http: // www. tshaonline. org / handbook / online / articles / fbi 21 (accessed 21 December 2019)." type="url" year="2016">Burke 2016</bibRefCitation>
), the type locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" box="[858,1013,1143,1169]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="birkmannii">
<emphasis box="[858,877,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[890,1013,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">birkmannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[1178,1396,1143,1169]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref22678" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[1259,1308,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
the type series is housed at 
<collectionCode box="[420,506,1179,1205]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">AMNH</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[562,626,1179,1205]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[689,787,1179,1205]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">syntypes</typeStatus>
deposited in those collections were found, as well as unnoticed primary types in 
<collectionCode box="[426,499,1215,1241]" country="Austria" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c7yt-hh77" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">NMW</collectionCode>
. The single 
<typeStatus box="[630,717,1215,1241]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">syntype</typeStatus>
female found in the 
<collectionCode box="[942,1028,1215,1241]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">AMNH</collectionCode>
is here designated the 
<typeStatus box="[1278,1384,1215,1241]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The chosen specimen has the following data label: 
